            "title": "ERWALDO Curaggio 1.0 First Generation NFC Reader",
            "handle": "professional-key-fob-duplicator-system",
            "description": "It operates on the common 125khz frequency used by the vast majority of residential and commercial security systems. To use it, simply hold your existing \"master\" fob against the sensor and press \"Read.\" Once you place a blank, rewritable tag against it and press \"write\" the device beeps and the LED indicators turn on to confirm it has captured the data. Specifically engineered to work with the industry-standard EM4305 and T5577 chips, covering the vast majority of proximity fobs used today. Total Portability, lightweight and ergonomically designed to fit comfortably in your hand.",
